		<div class='Inner'><div class="ColumnSection">
<p>The Vega Science Trust started recording video interviews with scientists and Nobel Laureates in the late 90`s.&nbsp; It is our aim not only to provide an outlet for video interviews with scientists discussing their research and the views but to provide a video archive for the future of some of our greatest scientists.<br /><br />These interviews have either been recorded as in-depth Face to Face interviews over an extended period of time or as shorter interviews recorded at the Lindau meeting of Nobel Laureates (described below).<br />&nbsp;</p><table width="100%"><tr><td class="table_top_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>Science Video Interviews Physics: Interviews with Bloembergen, Esaki, Giacconi, Giaever, Glauber, Koshiba, Kroemer, M&uuml;ller, Osheroff, Richardson, t&rsquo;Hooft and Veltman, Townes.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>Science Video Interviews Physics: Interviews with Bloembergen, Esaki, Giacconi, Giaever, Glauber, Koshiba, Kroemer, M&uuml;ller, Osheroff, Richardson, t&rsquo;Hooft and Veltman, Townes.</p>')" href="../subseries/5"><img height="100"  src="../../images/series_system/600px-Keplers_supernova.jpg_100x100.jpeg" width="100" border="0" /></a></td><td class="table_top_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>Science Video Interviews of Nobel Laureates in Medicine/Physiology: Interviews with Werner Arber, G&uuml;nter Blobel, Christian de Duve, Edmond Fischer, Erwin Neher, Marshall Nirenberg, Christiane N&uuml;sslein-Volhard, Bert Sakmann and Torsten Wiesel.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>Science Video Interviews of Nobel Laureates in Medicine/Physiology: Interviews with Werner Arber, G&uuml;nter Blobel, Christian de Duve, Edmond Fischer, Erwin Neher, Marshall Nirenberg, Christiane N&uuml;sslein-Volhard, Bert Sakmann and Torsten Wiesel.</p>')" href="../subseries/6"><img height="100"  src="../../images/series_system/150.tnbt.IR-human-body.jpg_100x100.jpeg" width="100" border="0" /></a></td><td class="table_top_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>A science video documentary following the experiences of 6 young Ph.D students who attend the Lindau meeting of Nobel Laureates in Medicine for the first time.&nbsp; Laureates include Torsten Wiesel and G&uuml;nter Blobel.&nbsp; Filmed in 2004.&nbsp; <br /><br />Commissioned by Vega and produced by Edward Goldwyn (Ex BBC Horizon/Nova) this interesting documentary gives us an inside view of a very special conference where Nobel Laureates gather in Lindau (Germany) with just one aim in mind - to meet young science students!</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>A science video documentary following the experiences of 6 young Ph.D students who attend the Lindau meeting of Nobel Laureates in Medicine for the first time.&nbsp; Laureates include Torsten Wiesel and G&uuml;nter Blobel.&nbsp; Filmed in 2004.&nbsp; <br /><br />Commissioned by Vega and produced by Edward Goldwyn (Ex BBC Horizon/Nova) this interesting documentary gives us an inside view of a very special conference where Nobel Laureates gather in Lindau (Germany) with just one aim in mind - to meet young science students!</p>')" href="../subseries/7"><img height="100"  src="../../images/series_system/Lindau.jpg_100x100.jpeg" width="100" border="0" /></a></td><td class="table_top_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>A collection of science video interviews with Nobel Prize winners in Chemistry. Chemistry Laureates interviewed include Cornforth, Crutzen, Eigen, Ernst, Klug, Kohn, Heeger, MacDiarmid, MacKinnon, Marcus, Perutz, Rowland, Sanger, Townes, W&uuml;therich.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>A collection of science video interviews with Nobel Prize winners in Chemistry. Chemistry Laureates interviewed include Cornforth, Crutzen, Eigen, Ernst, Klug, Kohn, Heeger, MacDiarmid, MacKinnon, Marcus, Perutz, Rowland, Sanger, Townes, W&uuml;therich.</p>')" href="../subseries/18"><img height="100"  src="../../images/series_system/chem3.jpg_100x100.jpeg" width="100" border="0" /></a></td></tr><tr><td class="table_bottom_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>Science Video Interviews Physics: Interviews with Bloembergen, Esaki, Giacconi, Giaever, Glauber, Koshiba, Kroemer, M&uuml;ller, Osheroff, Richardson, t&rsquo;Hooft and Veltman, Townes.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>Science Video Interviews Physics: Interviews with Bloembergen, Esaki, Giacconi, Giaever, Glauber, Koshiba, Kroemer, M&uuml;ller, Osheroff, Richardson, t&rsquo;Hooft and Veltman, Townes.</p>')" href="../subseries/5">Physics</a></td><td class="table_bottom_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>Science Video Interviews of Nobel Laureates in Medicine/Physiology: Interviews with Werner Arber, G&uuml;nter Blobel, Christian de Duve, Edmond Fischer, Erwin Neher, Marshall Nirenberg, Christiane N&uuml;sslein-Volhard, Bert Sakmann and Torsten Wiesel.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>Science Video Interviews of Nobel Laureates in Medicine/Physiology: Interviews with Werner Arber, G&uuml;nter Blobel, Christian de Duve, Edmond Fischer, Erwin Neher, Marshall Nirenberg, Christiane N&uuml;sslein-Volhard, Bert Sakmann and Torsten Wiesel.</p>')" href="../subseries/6">Medicine/Physiology</a></td><td class="table_bottom_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>A science video documentary following the experiences of 6 young Ph.D students who attend the Lindau meeting of Nobel Laureates in Medicine for the first time.&nbsp; Laureates include Torsten Wiesel and G&uuml;nter Blobel.&nbsp; Filmed in 2004.&nbsp; <br /><br />Commissioned by Vega and produced by Edward Goldwyn (Ex BBC Horizon/Nova) this interesting documentary gives us an inside view of a very special conference where Nobel Laureates gather in Lindau (Germany) with just one aim in mind - to meet young science students!</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>A science video documentary following the experiences of 6 young Ph.D students who attend the Lindau meeting of Nobel Laureates in Medicine for the first time.&nbsp; Laureates include Torsten Wiesel and G&uuml;nter Blobel.&nbsp; Filmed in 2004.&nbsp; <br /><br />Commissioned by Vega and produced by Edward Goldwyn (Ex BBC Horizon/Nova) this interesting documentary gives us an inside view of a very special conference where Nobel Laureates gather in Lindau (Germany) with just one aim in mind - to meet young science students!</p>')" href="../subseries/7">Lindau Documentary</a></td><td class="table_bottom_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>A collection of science video interviews with Nobel Prize winners in Chemistry. Chemistry Laureates interviewed include Cornforth, Crutzen, Eigen, Ernst, Klug, Kohn, Heeger, MacDiarmid, MacKinnon, Marcus, Perutz, Rowland, Sanger, Townes, W&uuml;therich.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>A collection of science video interviews with Nobel Prize winners in Chemistry. Chemistry Laureates interviewed include Cornforth, Crutzen, Eigen, Ernst, Klug, Kohn, Heeger, MacDiarmid, MacKinnon, Marcus, Perutz, Rowland, Sanger, Townes, W&uuml;therich.</p>')" href="../subseries/18">Chemistry</a></td></tr><tr><td class="table_top_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>A science video interview with physicist Joseph Rotblat joint Nobel Peace Prize Winner and co-founder of Pugwash the organisaiton that shared the Nobel Prize for&nbsp; efforts to diminish the part played by nuclear arms in international politics.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>A science video interview with physicist Joseph Rotblat joint Nobel Peace Prize Winner and co-founder of Pugwash the organisaiton that shared the Nobel Prize for&nbsp; efforts to diminish the part played by nuclear arms in international politics.</p>')" href="../subseries/19"><img height="100"  src="../../images/series_system/Rotblatnew.jpg_100x100.jpeg" width="100" border="0" /></a></td></tr><tr><td class="table_bottom_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>A science video interview with physicist Joseph Rotblat joint Nobel Peace Prize Winner and co-founder of Pugwash the organisaiton that shared the Nobel Prize for&nbsp; efforts to diminish the part played by nuclear arms in international politics.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>A science video interview with physicist Joseph Rotblat joint Nobel Peace Prize Winner and co-founder of Pugwash the organisaiton that shared the Nobel Prize for&nbsp; efforts to diminish the part played by nuclear arms in international politics.</p>')" href="../subseries/19">Peace</a></td></tr></table><p>The Lindau Meeting - each year some thirty or more Nobel laureates come to Lindau to give lectures and interact with about 1000 young scientists from around the world.&nbsp; In any one year the focus is generally on one area eg. chemistry, physics, medicine or economics.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><br />&nbsp;<br /><br /><span class="bold_title">Links To Other Information:</span><p /><strong><a href="http://www.lindau-nobel.de/">The Lindau Website</a></strong><br />The official Lindau website<p /><strong><a href="http://nobelprize.org/">e nobel museum</a></strong><br />The official website of the Nobel Foundation</div>
